headline: NetApp (NASDAQ:NTAP) Beats Q4 CY2025 Sales Expectations
summary: Data storage company NetApp (NASDAQ:NTAP) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 4.4% year on year to $1.71 billion. On top of that, next quarter’s revenue guidance ($1.87 billion at the midpoint) was surprisingly good and 4% above what analysts were expecting. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.12 per share was 2.8% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Pure Storage Slides Despite Rebranded Everpure's Earnings Beat. Here's What Wall Street Is Saying.
summary: Pure Storage stock reversed sharply lower Thursday, despite the enterprise data storage provider's fiscal Q4 results topping expectations.  The earnings report comes the same week the company announced a rebrand to the name Everpure.  Everpure on Wednesday reported adjusted earnings of 69 cents per share for the Feb. 1-ended quarter, up 53% from a year earlier.
